<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-573-742  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 573 742.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 29 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Versatile Mac screen saver. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Berkeley Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   After Dark (Utility program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Utility ProgramsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VERSATILE MAC SCREEN SAVER BERKELEY, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1989 AUG 25 (NB) --Macintosh users need no longer be confined to watching tiny fireworks explodeor stars whip past their screen when their screen saver, designed to preventscreen burn-in, is activated.andP;  A new product from Berkeley Systems provides avariety of screen-savers with everything from shifting moire patterns tolightening bolts to drifting corporate logos.andP;  After Dark, $39.95, providesmultiple graphic modules.andP;  A business- oriented module allows companies toscan in their corporate logo, which will then drift about the screen when thescreen saver engages, a feature which might be attractive to companies whichkeep their unattended Macs in the public eye.andP;  There are also screen saversthat offer a night sky with streaking meteors, rain drops, flashinglightening bolts, crawling worms, or a basic dimmer.andP;  The product also has an&quot;anti-snoop&quot; feature which prevents the machine from reawakening without apassword.andP;  (Wendy Woods/19890825/Press Contact: Nicholas Rush, 415-540- 5535)</TEXT></DOC>